Yasser Arafat Tuesday accused the United States of threatening to kill
PLO officials if Palestinian guerillas attack American
targets. Denying the accusation, the State Department explained that
it had received reports that the PLO might target Americans because of
alleged U.S. involvement in the assassination of Khalil Wazir (code
name Abu Jihad), the PLO's second in command. (Wazir was killed April
16 during a raid on his house near Tunis, Tunisia.) Arafat took
U.S. denial of any involvement in the assassination and warning that
the PLO would be held accountable for any action against U.S.
personnel to be a threat to assassinate PLO leaders.</SUM>

