Col. Herminio Taylo, 54, police chief of Makati, Philippines was
assassinated today. The assassins identified themselves as members of
the New People's Army, the same group that claimed responsibility for
the April 21 assassination of Col. Rowe of the Joint U.S. Military
Assistance Group. Taylo was the tenth soldier or policeman slain in
the Manilla area in the last two weeks. President Corazon Aquino,
whose husband Benigno was assassinated in 1983, expressed her sympathy
for the family of Col. Taylo. National Security Adviser Rafael Ileto
said the killing showed that every soldier and policeman was a
potential target of assassination.</SUM>

