DOCREF="AP900428-0108"
SELECTOR="G"
SUMMARIZER="A"> 

Less than a month before elections, a third presidential candidate in
Colombia has been assassinated. A gunman on a suicide mission shot
Carlos Pizarro, candidate of the leftist April 19 Movement, or M-10,
on a jetliner Thursday.  Sen. Luis Carlos Galan of the ruling Liberal
Party was assassinated in Bogota last August and Bernardo Jaramillo of
the leftist Patriotic Union Party was killed last month at the Bogota
airport. Authorities have blamed the assassinations on drug
traffickers. Official investigations have shown that some members of
the Colombian armed forces are allied with drug traffickers and
right-wing death squads.</SUM>

