Last week the number two official in Mexico's ruling Institutional
Revolutionary Party (PRI) was assassinated. The killing of Jose
Francisco Ruiz Massieu was allegedly ordered by Manuel Munoz Rocha, a
federal deputy of the PRI and Abraham Rubio Canales, a former tourism
developer with strong links to the Gulf drug cartel in the state of
Tamaulipas. Munoz Rocha has admitted to a role in the crime but put
the responsibility on Rubio Canales. Political reactionaries and drug
traffickers are thought to have played a role in the killing six
months ago of the PRI's reform-minded presidential candidate Luis
Donaldo Colosio.</SUM>

