Lebanese and Jordanian authorities have unraveled the mystery
surrounding the assassination of Jordanian diplomat Na'ib al-
Ma'ayitah in Beirut on 29 January.  It appears that the Abu-Nidal
group, the prime suspects in the assassination, was not acting
alone. There was close coordination between the Fatah-- the
Revolutionary Council (FRC) of the Abu-Nidal group and Jordanian
fundamentalist extremist groups sponsored by Iran, specifically the
Jordanian fundamentalist Islamic Mobilization Youth Organization
(IMYO) which is financed by Iran. The assassins received training at
an Abu-Nidal center in Lebanon from a Palestinian expert in
assassinations who was implicated in the assassination of FRC official
Bahij Abu-al-Hana in July 19 92.</SUM>

