There has been widespread international reaction to the assassination
of Luis Donaldo Colosio Murrieta, presidential candidate for the
Mexican Institutional Revolutionary Party (PRI) on March 233 in
Tijuana. The Colombian Government and several presidential candidates
expressed their regrets and condemned such violence. A spokesman for
the Cuban Foreign ministry extended the sympathy of the Cuban people
to the Mexican Government and people. In El Salvador leaders of the
ruling Arena Party and of the opposition coalition expressed
condolences and condemned the cowardly act. Venezuela's Foreign
Minister deplored the assassination and expressed his sadness over the
incident.</SUM>

